HEADWORD: Groundly
<hw>Ground"ly</hw>, <pos>adv.</pos> <def>Solidly; deeply;
thoroughly.</def> <mark>[Obs.]</mark>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>Those whom princes do once <qex>groundly</qex> hate, Let them
provide to die as sure us fate.</q> <rj><qau>Marston.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Groundnut</ent>⟦br⟧
